[normal]&#xa0;[bold]2.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Global Partnership for Education
[normal] 
[normal](GPE) 
[normal]is 
[normal]the 
[normal]only multilateral [bold]partnership devoted to getting [bold]all [bold]children into school for a [bold]good [bold]quality education[bold]. The Global Partnership 
[normal]– made up of governments, civil society organizations, international 
[normal]institutions, teachers, private foundations, and the private sector – provides funding to support the development and implementation of high-quality education sector plans
[normal] 
[normal]in the w
[normal]orld’s poorest countries and  helps
[normal] 
[normal]coordinate support arou
[normal]nd those plans.
[normal] F
[normal]undamental to the
[normal] Global Partnership’s work is ensuring
[normal] education 
[normal]sector 
[normal]plans
[normal] 
[normal]are 
[normal]inclusive and 
[normal]meet the educational 
[normal]needs 
[normal]of all children
[normal]. 
[normal]In its report to the UN Secretary General in May 2013, the 
[normal]United Nations High-Level Panel of Eminent Persons on [bold]the Post-2015 Development Agenda[bold] highlighted:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]‘The Global Partnership for Education is getting quality education to marginalized children, coordinating education’s many players, offering aid without wasteful replication, and following local leadership’
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.2
[normal]              
[normal]With the support of the UK and a number of other donor partners, the 
[normal]Global Partnership has[bold] 
[normal]transformed international cooperation[bold] in education in developing countries.
[normal] Since 2002, it has helped to pioneer the coordination of development partners in support of nationally owned 
[normal]and implemented education sector plans. In doing so, the GPE has 
[normal]improved the alignment of external 
[normal]technical and financial resources with sustain
[normal]able
[normal], nationally relevant
[normal] education strategies
[normal]. Due to the value of GPE processes in improving education development and the catalytic impact of GPE financing on system strengthening in the education sector, GPE has become one of the most significant sourc
[normal]es of education financing for the poorest countries in the world. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.3
[normal]              
[normal]Since 2009, 
[normal]the Global Partnership has [bold]implemented[bold] widespread[bold] 
[normal]reforms to further strengthen the partnership[bold] and help it to [bold]deliver [bold]better [bold]results.[bold] 
[normal]The
[normal] 
[normal]UK MAR
[normal] 
[normal]2013 Update
[normal] ranks GPE progress 
[normal]against 
[normal]the MAR reform priorities as the fourth highest 
[normal]of all multilateral organizations 
[normal]assessed in
[normal] the original review
[normal]. 
[normal]Further revisions
[normal] are planned including of the GPE Fund 
[normal]to ensure it 
[normal]respond
[normal]s
[normal] to the increase in
[normal] demand for
[normal] 
[normal]fun
[normal]ding in the most effective and efficient way
[normal]. 
[normal]New commitments
[normal] from the UK and other donor partners for the repleni
[normal]shment of the Global Partnership
[normal] for the pe
[normal]riod 2015 – 2018 
[normal]will help 
[normal]further 
[normal]accelerate 
[normal]developing country 
[normal]progress towards ensuring 
[normal]all
[normal] chil
[normal]dren receive a
[normal] quality education, in
[normal]cluding children with disabilities
[normal] and other marginalized
[normal] groups
[normal].
