[normal]3.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The GPE [bold]Strategic Plan [bold]2012 – 2015 commits t[bold]he partnership to support [bold]children who are [bold]the [bold]most marginalized[bold] and 
[normal]to 
[normal]building national systems that have the capacity and integrity to deliver, support and assess quality education for all
[normal], including
[normal] children with disability
[normal]. 
[normal]T
[normal]he GPE strategic
[normal] goals are
[normal] access for all, learning for all, reachi
[normal]ng every child, and building for the
[normal] future. The 
[normal]Implementation Plan for GPE’s Strategic Plan includes a specific outcome on the access of children with disabilities to inclusive and quality learning. It further com
[normal]mits GPE and its partners to support the creation of inclusive educa
[normal]tion systems, in particular: 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]environments f
[normal]or children with disabilities
[normal]effective
[normal]ne
[normal]ss to improve learning outcomes for marginalized children, in particular children with disabilities.
